tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows hypoglycemia, low HbA1c, elevated creatinine, and significant proteinuria, suggesting possible renal impairment. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, high protein, glucose, and ketones) may indicate nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy, though diabetes is unlikely given low glucose/HbA1c. No evidence of urinary infection. Further nephrological evaluation and assessment for other causes of proteinuria and renal dysfunction are recommended.
